Usage instructions for webGME

1. Installation:
    - fetch the latest version from git directly and start using it (check the package.json for other node package dependencies!!!)
    - install it with npm ('npm install webgme'), and you are ready to go

2. Program Usage:
    !!! all runnable function are stored in the bin directory !!!
    - combined_server : this program runs an http server plus an additional webgme server as well ('node bin/combined_server.js')

3. Library Usage:
    - birck by birck:
        ...
        var webGME = require('webgme');
        var storage = new webgme.storage.mongo({host:'my database address', port:'port to communicate with mongoDB' });
        storage.openDatabase(function(err){
            if(!err){
                //put your function here
            }
        });
        ...

